 of archival material and other texts to determine the causal role radical right parties play in influencing parties, policies and ultimately democratic quality in the seven countries.Depleting democracies advances theory on radical right actors in the political process and contributes to empirical research across the region. Its results are particularly relevant to the debate on democratic transformation and the effects of radical right parties.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  aViktor Orbán.  aasylum policy.  acontagion effects.  acordon sanitaire.  ademocratic backsliding.  adepletion.  aethnocentrism.  aidentity politics.  ailliberal democracy.  aminority politics.1 aMinkenberg, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVégh, Zsuzsanna, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVégh, Zsuzsanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packagez9783111206455oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152616019540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526160195423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526160195/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPb2023